### Module 7 — Sessions & Cookies
### NOTE: VS Code REST Client handles cookies automatically between requests.
### With curl, use: curl -c cookies.txt (save) and curl -b cookies.txt (send)

@base = http://localhost:3000

# ─── Try protected route without a session ───────────────

### Should return 401
GET {{base}}/dashboard


# ─── Login ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Login — observe the Set-Cookie header in the response!
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "james@example.com", "password": "password123" }

###
# curl -v -c cookies.txt -X POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"email":"james@example.com","password":"password123"}'
# Watch for: Set-Cookie: connect.sid=s%3A...


# ─── Authenticated requests ──────────────────────────────

### Get current user (session cookie sent automatically by REST Client)
GET {{base}}/auth/me

### Protected dashboard
GET {{base}}/dashboard

### Increment login count — stored in session
PUT {{base}}/auth/me/increment
###
PUT {{base}}/auth/me/increment
### Get me again — loginCount should have increased
GET {{base}}/auth/me

###
# curl -b cookies.txt http://localhost:3000/auth/me
# curl -b cookies.txt http://localhost:3000/dashboard


# ─── Wrong credentials ────────────────────────────────────

### Wrong password — generic error (no enumeration)
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "james@example.com", "password": "wrong" }


# ─── Logout ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### Logout — clears cookie
POST {{base}}/auth/logout

### Now /me should return 401 again
GET {{base}}/auth/me

###
# curl -v -c cookies.txt -b cookies.txt -X POST http://localhost:3000/auth/logout
